Description: Ostracon, fragment of the body of a red-brown pottery grooved vessel, the fabric is grey in section, the interior bears the remains of five lines of black-painted demotic text, the exterior is covered with a self-slip and very faint traces of a further six lines of black-painted demotic text.
Curator's comments: Being studied for publication by Bryan Kraemer. Cemeteries and Osireion Excavations Group
Bibliographic references: Frankfort 1933 / The Cenotaph of Seti I at Abydos (no.1 (p.95,pl.xciii)) (Exterior side)
Jasnow & Pouls Wegner 2006-2007 / Demotic Ostraca from North Abydos (p. 49) (Exterior side)
